M||tx|---
M||titl|Use Compound cp
M||impa|hi
M||impa|enables flexible composition w/o prop drilling
M||tags|composition, compound-cp, architecture
M||tx|---
M|Use |tx|Structure complex cp as compound cp w/ a shared context. Each
M|Use |tx|subcomponent accesses shared state via context, not props. Consumers compose the
M|Use |tx|pieces they need.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|fn Composer({
M|Use |tx|renderHeader,
M|Use |tx|renderFooter,
M|Use |tx|renderActions,
M|Use |tx|showAttachments,
M|Use |tx|showFormatting,
M|Use |tx|showEmojis,
M|Use |}|Props) {
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<form>
M|Use |tx|{renderHeader?.()}
M|Use |tx|<Input />
M|Use |tx|{showAttachments && <Attachments />}
M|Use |tx|{renderFooter ? (
M|Use |tx|renderFooter()
M|Use |)|(
M|Use |tx|<Footer>
M|Use |tx|{showFormatting && <Formatting />}
M|Use |tx|{showEmojis && <Emojis />}
M|Use |tx|{renderActions?.()}
M|Use |tx|</Footer>
M|Use |tx|)}
M|Use |tx|</form>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|const ComposerContext = createContext<ComposerContextValue \| null>(null)
M|Use |func|ProviderProps) {
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<ComposerContext value={{ state, actions, meta }}>
M|Use |tx|{children}
M|Use |tx|</ComposerContext>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|Use |tx|return <form>{children}</form>
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|fn ComposerInput() {
M|Use |tx|const {
M|Use |tx|state,
M|Use |acti|{ up },
M|Use |meta|{ inputRef },
M|Use |tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<TextInput
M|Use |tx|ref={inputRef}
M|Use |tx|value={state.input}
M|Use |onCh|text }))}
M|Use |tx|/>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|fn ComposerSubmit() {
M|Use |tx|const {
M|Use |acti|{ submit },
M|Use |tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|Use |tx|return <Button onPress={submit}>Send</Button>
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|// Export as compound cp
M|Use |tx|const Composer = {
M|Use |pr|ComposerProvider,
M|Use |Fram|ComposerFrame,
M|Use |Inpu|ComposerInput,
M|Use |Subm|ComposerSubmit,
M|Use |Head|ComposerHeader,
M|Use |Foot|ComposerFooter,
M|Use |Atta|ComposerAttachments,
M|Use |Form|ComposerFormatting,
M|Use |Emoj|ComposerEmojis,
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Us|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|<Composer.pr state={state} actions={actions} meta={meta}>
M|Use |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Use |tx|<Composer.Header />
M|Use |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|Use |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|Use |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|Use |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|Use |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|Use |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Use |tx|</Composer.pr>
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |tx|Consumers explicitly compose exactly what they need. No hidden conditionals. And the state, actions and meta are dependency-injected by a parent pr, allowing multiple usages of the same cp structure.